values: I got a new bike.  It is a Mongoose RX-150.  See the pics because it kicks ass.  I rode it four miles yesterday and got a bunch of messed up gears, four miles today and a flat tire, hopefully nothing bad tomorrow.  I fucking hate women that put me down because my friends have small penises.

OK, here is the official update info on my cashout for graduation: $220, cash ($150 already spent on mongoose mountain bike); microwave; leather planner; printer; lots of leftover food from the reception.  I made "GED Student of the Year", and was elected from about 70 attending graduates.  I also was honored as a "High Scoring GED", which means a score placing in the 85th percentile.  I think that is as far as my achievements go so far, but I will keep you updated as my life progresses.

So, it is now 5:00 in the morning, do you know where your children are?  I graduated yesterday, and yet I wonder whether I am ready for that symbolic transition. I have spent the last 17 years of my life trying to remain just a child, I wonder what will become of me...

HAHA.  Once again I seem to have found myself at arms with fighting for the physical world and the world in my head.  I am new to livejournal, so just keep with me.  Any beautiful women who are missing a man I'm here for ya.  Later, peace out.
